# Docker Compose — always restart after relevant edits

This app is normally run via `docker compose` in the repo root.

Whenever you change anything that affects the running container (including but not limited to `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `app/`, `static/`, `.env` values loaded by Compose, or `requirements.txt`), **before you finish the task**:

1. Run from the project root: `docker compose up -d --build`
2. Confirm the command succeeded (containers recreated/started as needed).

Do not assume the user will restart manually; apply the new code and env by recreating the service yourself.
